SolidWorks is a computer-aided design software which is used to perform tasks on design. Automotive industries implement SolidWorks when structuring or planning a design of a car or an automotive part. SolidWorks accepts input from users, analyse it and applies artificial intelligence (AI) to generate the desired output. Engineers often use this technology to help them come with better designs and redesigning a project. The use of SolidWorks is not just limited to construction and automobile. Its aptness in design can also be employed in mechanical and aerospace technology.

SolidWorks has also earned its fame as computer-aided engineering (CAE). It is developed with an intention to run on windows operating system. Dassault System first generated and released SolidWorks. Information about SolidWorks can also be availed by online SolidWorks assignment help.
